#!/usr/bin/env Rscript

# =============================================================================
# STANDALONE TE-TL / TL-AE REVERSAL ANALYSIS
#
# Uses the saved full DEG tables from the filtered robust edgeR analyses.
#
# Calculates:
#   1. Retention of sex-adjusted DEGs in the unadjusted analysis
#   2. Unadjusted and sex-adjusted reversal-gene counts
#   3. Directional subdivision of reversal genes
#   4. Direction-specific one-sided Fisher exact tests
#   5. Overlap between unadjusted and sex-adjusted reversal sets
#   6. Recovery of lost genes at sex-adjusted FDR < 0.05
#   7. Preservation of logFC directions after sex adjustment
#
# Contrast definitions:
#   TE_vs_TL = TE - TL
#   TL_vs_AE = TL - AE
#
# Biological interpretation:
#   TE_vs_TL logFC < 0:
#       expression is higher in TL than TE
#       = increased from early to late torpor
#
#   TL_vs_AE logFC > 0:
#       expression is higher in TL than AE
#       = decreased at arousal onset
# =============================================================================


